Class FrameChain

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static FrameChain create(Frame source,
                                Frame target)
        Creates a new immutable frame chain instance from a source frame to a target frame.

        The frame chain will represent the shortest path from the source to the target frame and will provide methods for querying the frames and connections on this path. Transformations can be computed between neighboring frames on the path or for the whole path.

        Caution: The caller should make sure that the frame tree is not modified between creating an instance of this class and calling the methods that query the connection.

        This methods locks both the frame tree of the source frame and the frame tree of the target frame during the creation of the frame chain using the lock returned by Frame.getFrameTreeLock(). If the Frames that are passed in are thread safe (e.g. ObjectFrames), the frame tree traversal is guaranteed to be thread safe. Otherwise, if the implementation is not thread safe (e.g. LocalFrame), thread safety will have to be taken care of by the caller.

        Parameters:
        source - the source of the frame chain. Can be queried later by getSourceFrame(). If null, the top-level parent frame will be used as source.
        target - the target of the frame chain. Can be queried later by getTargetFrame(). If null, the top-level parent frame will be used as target.
        Returns:
        the FrameChain between source and target, or null if the two frames are not connected.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if both arguments are null

      • create

        public static FrameChain create(FrameChainElement source,
                                FrameChainElement target)
        Create a new immutable frame chain instance that represents a copy or a sub-chain of an existing frame chain.

        The new frame chain is defined by a source element and a target element that both belong to an existing frame chain. The new frame chain can correspond to a full copy of the old chain, or it can correspond to a sub-path on this frame chain. The path direction can be inverted when switching the order of source and target frame chain elements.

        This method will not lock the frame tree as only a copy of an existing immutable frame chain is generated.

        Use this method if you need to query sub-parts of an existing frame chain to avoid creating a new (and potentially inconsistent) snapshot from the frame tree.

        Parameters:
        source - the element of the frame chain that should be the new source element
        target - the element of the frame chain that should be the new target element
        Returns:
        the FrameChain between source and target.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if any of the arguments is null, or if the source and target elements do not correspond to the identical frame chain

      • getTransformation

        public Transformation getTransformation()
        This method calculates the transformation from source frame to target frame.

        If this chain includes IQueryConnections, it is up to the ITrafoQueryProcessor implementations(s) whether they support a default QueryType. Robot flange processors usually use QueryType.MEASURED.

        Returns:
        the transformation of the given type, expressed in the coordinate system of the source frame, as given to this class' constructor.
        Throws:
        ThreadInterruptedException - if the thread was interrupted during execution. The thread interrupt flag will be set if the thread was interrupted (that is, Thread.isInterrupted() will return true)
        TrafoQueryException - if a frame connection could not be queried for the current transformation
        IllegalStateException - if an unknown IFrameConnection is found, or if the frames given in the constructor have no connection
        See Also:
        isConnected(), getTransformation(QueryType)

      • getTransformation

        public Transformation getTransformation(QueryType queryType)
        This method calculates the transformation from source frame to target frame using the following methods:
        • For each ITransformationConnection, ITransformationConnection.getTransformationFromParent() will be used in the calculation.
        • For each IQueryConnection, the corresponding ITrafoQueryProcessor will be queried in the way described in the class description for the connection's current transformation of the given QueryType.
        • Other connection types are not recognized and result in an exception.
        Parameters:
        queryType - the type of transformation to query from the sensors. The query type must be a value that all query processors support, possibly including null to choose the processor's default (see getTransformation()).
        Returns:
        the transformation of the given type, expressed in the coordinate system of the source frame, as given to this class' constructor.
        Throws:
        ThreadInterruptedException - if the thread was interrupted during execution. The thread interrupt flag will be set if the thread was interrupted (that is, Thread.isInterrupted() will return true)
        TrafoQueryException - if querying a connection's transformation failed (the first occurrence will be found in the Throwable.getCause())
        IllegalStateException - if an unknown IFrameConnection is found, or if the frames given in the constructor have no connection
        See Also:
        isConnected(), getTransformation()

      • getTransformations

        public Map<QueryType,Transformation> getTransformations(Collection<? extends QueryType> queryTypes,
                                                        Object queryContext)
        This method calculates the transformation from source frame to target frame for each of the given QueryTypes, using the following methods:
        • For each ITransformationConnection, ITransformationConnection.getTransformationFromParent() will be used in the calculation.
        • For each IQueryConnection, the corresponding ITrafoQueryProcessor.processQuery(Collection, List, Object) method will be called.
        • Other connection types are not recognized and result in an exception.
        Parameters:
        queryTypes - a collection of QueryTypes that will be passed to the ITrafoQueryProcessors, if any IQueryConnections are present in the connection chain. The collection may only contain values that all query processors support, possibly including the null value.
        queryContext - an arbitrary object that will be passed to the ITrafoQueryProcessor.processQuery(Collection, List, Object) method of each query processor present in the connection chain. May be null.
        Returns:
        a map containing an ITransformation for each distinct value of the given query types. The transformations are expressed in the coordinate system of the source frame, as given to this class' constructor.
        Throws:
        ThreadInterruptedException - if the thread was interrupted during execution. The thread interrupt flag will be set if the thread was interrupted (that is, Thread.isInterrupted() will return true)
        TrafoQueryException - if querying a connection's transformation failed (the first occurrence will be found in the Throwable.getCause())
        IllegalStateException - if an unknown IFrameConnection is found, or if the frames given in the constructor have no connection
        See Also:
        isConnected(), getTransformation(), getTransformation(QueryType)
